    marketBackground: "",
    detailedAnalysis: "## Introduction to SpaceX IPO\nSpaceX's IPO is a highly anticipated event that is set to make history. The company, founded by Elon Musk, has been at the forefront of space technology and innovation, and its IPO is expected to be one of the largest ever. \n## Financial Performance\nSpaceX's revenue has grown by 50% annually for the past three years, driven by its successful satellite launches and spacecraft development. The company has also made significant investments in its infrastructure, including the development of its Starship program. \n## Investor Interest\nThe IPO has sparked intense interest among retail investors, with some brokerages reporting a 500% increase in account openings. Institutional investors are also showing strong interest, and the IPO is expected to be oversubscribed. According to Tom Barton, an analyst at investment firm, Jefferies, 'SpaceX's IPO is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity for investors to get in on the ground floor of a company that is revolutionizing the space industry.'\n\n---\n\nAuthor: Shiva Sandeep\n\nTelegram: @its_terabyte\n\nWhatsApp:\n\n*Default WhatsApp profile image placeholder*\n\nPublished by PulseTrends\n\n---",
